gnome-disk-utility 3.3.92
-------------------------

The gnome-disk-utility project provides the Disks application for
dealing with storage devices. It relies on the udisks project.

Changes since gnome-disk-utility 3.3.91:

 David Zeuthen (9):
       Post-release version bump to version 3.3.92
       Use units in application provided CSS to shut up recent GTK+ warning
       Rearrange dialog used for editing /etc/fstab entries
       Clean up options offered in fstab dialog, in particular negate 'noauto'
       Fix bug when updating negative checkbutton options
       Use proper capitalization for "Edit mount options..." menu item
       Also clean up crypttab dialog
       fstab: Show "Mount Point" before the device
       Update NEWS for release

 Updated translations: Ask H. Larsen, Daniel Mustieles, Daniel
   Nylander, Dr.T.Vasudevan, Fran Diéguez, Ivaylo Valkov, Matej
